  "texts": [
    "Figure 9 provides a visual representation of KNN algorithms.",
    "It can be applied to both regression and classification tasks in machine learning.",
    "KNN operates on the assumption that observations close in the attribute space (e.g., concrete mix properties) are also close to each other in terms of output values.",
    "Predictions for output values are made by using a predefined function of the response values of the nearest neighbors, with a focus on the closest neighbors in the data space.",
    "In standard KNN, the average function is commonly used."
  ],
